<doc id="485410" wikidata="Q17100343" url="?curid=485410" title="Irish Statute Book">
<text>The Irish Statute Book, also known as the electronic Irish Statute Book (eISB), is a database produced by the Office of the Attorney General of Ireland. It contains copies of Acts of the Oireachtas and statutory instruments. It also contains a Legislation Directory which includes chronological tables of pre-1922 legislation. It is published on a website (irishstatutebook.ie) and was formerly published on CD-ROM.

In 2001, the &quot;Irish Law Times&quot; said that, whilst the Attorney General&#x27;s staff deserved to be congratulated for the Irish Statute Book, the CD-ROM version contained a &quot;significant number of errors&quot;.

==See also==
*Law of the Republic of Ireland

